# Atomic Commits (Automatic)

Create git commits automatically when you finish work. **Do not wait for the user to ask.**

## Rules

- One logical unit of work per commit (see AGENTS.md §10)
- Commit each completed task before starting the next unrelated one
- Split multi-item audits (e.g. TD-043, TD-044) into separate commits per item or tightly related group
- Run tests/typecheck when practical before committing
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, credentials)
- Never push unless explicitly requested

## Commit messages

Use conventional prefixes: `fix`, `refactor`, `i18n`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`. Include TD/issue IDs when applicable.
